                          **************************
                          **  HEYSOFT's  TRUBBEL  **
                          ************************** 

WHAT ?
  A little game made after a TV-game seen on a Belgian tv-channel.
   (Made in Amos) 

WHY ?
  ???  (Because programming is fun.)

WORKS HOW ?
  On titlescreen push a mousebutton for playing with, or use keyboard to play
  without music.
  Choose English (e) or Netherlands (n) text.
  Next type (1) for computer opponent or (2) to play agains a friend (or enemy).
  After typing your name (max. 10 char's), type a number between 1 and 5,to
  choose howmany sets you want in a game. {1=3;2=5;3=7;4=9;5=11}
    (for instance to play 'the best of 7 sets' type 3.)
  The aim is ,of course, to win the most sets. A set is won by finding 3 of the 5
  marked icons. [Is possible that max. 2 marked icons are visible.]
  The player who's name is highlighted choose a number between 1 and 9. (the board
  is made like the numberblock on your keyboard, but the normale key's also works)
  You have a few seconds to choose ,otherwise the opponent plays.
  After the game you can push Return or 'j' to restart. Push 'n' to quit and 
  return to workbench.

WHO ?
  Enter 'info' as playersname !  (music by ???)

WORKS ON ?
  Amiga's with more than 1Mb memory. (A4000.30|.40|.60 ???)

WHEN ?
  15/11/1996

